original: Hultgren, Nils Per Gösta, sektions-ingenjör, Lyckoi-iia, f. 7/7/06 i Sthdm av sjökapt. Nils H. o. Anna Pettersson. G. 30 m. Gertrud Göhle. Barn: Boinniey f. 31, Rodh 41, Tedh 44. — Realex. 22, ing. STI 25, stud :ex. 26, civ:ing. 30. Res. t. Engl., Frankr., Belg., Holl. 25-27, Tyskl., Schweiz, Österr. 30. Anst. v. Luth & Roséns el. verikst. 23-24, v. teilegr:verket fr. 31, sekt :ing. i Uddevalilia fr. 45.
translated: Hultgren, Nils Per Gösta was a section engineer from Lyckorna. He was born on July 7th, 1906 in Stockholm to a sea captain named Nils Hultgren and Anna Pettersson. He was married to Gertrud Göhle in 1930, and they had three children: Boinniey (born in 1931), Rodh (born in 1941), and Tedh (born in 1944). Hultgren completed his real exam at the age of 22, STI engineering degree in 1925, and then studied at university in 1926. He received his civil engineering degree in 1930. He traveled to England, France, Belgium, Holland from 1925-1927 and then to Germany, Switzerland, and Austria in 1930. Hultgren was employed at Luth & Rosén Electrical Works from 1923-1924 and then at the telegraph company from 1931. He became a section engineer in Uddevalla from 1945.
